        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2019-05-08">
        <p itemprop="description">I brought my car to flushing tire to get my inspection done a couple of days ago.  One of the employees said my rear brake pads and rotors needed to be replaced and or it won&#39;t pass inspection.  Another gentleman who normally sits inside the little booth in the corner and usually wears a button down shirt gave me a price quote.  Any smart consumer wants to save money so I decided to do it myself as it&#39;s not too complicated of a job.

It was interesting to note that the old rotors were actually in not too bad of shape.  There were no grooves and they still had not reached minimal thickness but there was some normal rusting around the outer edges.  I decided to change them anyway and once the rotors and pads were replaced I brought it back to the shop to get the inspection done.  The same gentleman approached me and asked me with an attitude, how come the shop who replaced my brakes didn&#39;t do my inspection.  When I told him that I replaced them myself he told me he&#39;s not doing the inspection.  I asked why not and he just replied with &#34;no&#34; and turned his back to me and walked away, no explanation whatsoever.

I&#39;ve been coming to this shop for a few years now getting common services done like oil changes, inspections, flat tire repair.  To have him refuse service to my car because I simply decided to change my own brakes instead of paying him is really unprofessional.  It&#39;s not too big of a deal for me since there are hundreds of other shops who will do my inspection but there are 3 other vehicles in my household and you just lost our business for all our vehicles.<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Yang W.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="5.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2019-05-08">
        <p itemprop="description">Affordable price, I got my X3 run flat swapped to regular tire with wheel alignment for only 45 bucks<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Ronghuan C.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="1.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2019-02-10">
        <p itemprop="description">My friends went there for a tire repair and that&#39;s all he needed. However, staff started to recommend my friends to get a new tire. My friends refused to do so and left. Later on my friends found some new Damages on the tire so they realized it was a scam, truth story.<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Ellie W.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="5.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-07-30">
        <p itemprop="description">Zack &amp; guys saved the day!!! I had not one but TWO flat tires!! Very expensive for a new car, but they fixed them right up, no new tires for me &amp; I was on my way!!!
They got me right in with lots of smiles all around, they were swamped but took care of everyone SO quickly and most importantly, I felt safe.
They&#39;re AWESOME!!! Best tire repair place in a jiffy!!<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Jennifer C.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="5.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2019-02-03">
        <p itemprop="description">This auto repair shop is fantastic. I have a BMW X3 with run-flat tires and being that it was a Sunday I couldn&#39;t call Rallye nor could I schedule a service appointment for the very next day because they were booked. Although the shop itself looks a bit shabby, I decided to give it a try based on the outstanding reviews. I went there thinking I would have to buy a brand new tire and spending over $300 because that&#39;s what Rallye made me do historically. Rallye said run-flats weren&#39;t repairable. As soon as I got there I was assisted immediately. The guy could have scammed me and charged me $355 for a brand new tire but instead he was super honest and said that all I needed was patch work. I ended up spending less than 10 minutes there and paid $20 for my tire. I definitely recommend this place!<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Louann C.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="5.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2019-06-02">
        <p itemprop="description">I&#39;m sorry I would have given Zach 10 stars out of 5 I realized when I posted this in March I made a mistake on the stars my apologies but he still is the BEST<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Michael L.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="5.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2019-02-11">
        <p itemprop="description">My wife and I have been coming here for 10 yrs or so and have never had a problem or complaint. The prices, quality of work and service are 2nd to none and we only come here for any work or servicing we need for our cars. They are straight forward about what needs to be fixed and what the best course of action is. The owners and employees have always been welcoming and helpful.<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Gloria N.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="5.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-08-09">
        <p itemprop="description">My mom always comes here and loves the service, so here I am. I came for a leaking tire, which was due to the beautiful roads in NYC (&amp; my bad habits of hitting every pothole as if for fun), and I was assisted immediately. I simply told the kind worker which tire needed to be repaired and he got right to it. He found two nails and inserted plugs in under 10 minutes, for a very very reasonable price ($10 per plug). I would recommend everyone to come here, as the service is quick and great, and the prices are very reasonable.<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Arnold B.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="5.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-08-12">
        <p itemprop="description">The tire work performed at this place is so fast and the prices are so fair that I don&#39;t even try and haggle with them anymore. I&#39;ve been going here for about ten years. The two guys in charge are there every single day busting their butts. I appreciate their work ethic.<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Andre F.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="5.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-09-04">
        <p itemprop="description">This guy Zack knows his stuff. Literally took him 10 min to determine I had 2 bad tires. Trust this guy&#39;s.<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Rifi B.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="5.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2019-01-10">
        <p itemprop="description">Excellent place for all your tire needs. Went here twice, once for tire rotation and second to balance and mount 2 tires. They were open on New Year&#39;s day when other shops were closed. Also best prices in the city for quality work.<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="SkyeBlue B.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="5.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2017-05-29">
        <p itemprop="description">Got two flat tires from the Flushing Meadows Park. The guys at the shop waited for me even though they&#39;re about to closed! They even told me to be careful , not to rush. Lifesavers! Excellent customer services. Great job.
Extra gratitude to Jorgito!<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Alice M.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="5.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-02-02">
        <p itemprop="description">Last month, I called a few days in advance and spoke to Zack, the owner, directly about an annual car inspection (car newbie here and my year 1 was coming up). He reassured me about the times that he&#39;d be on-site and the standard cost.

A few days later, I drove over with my dad and my car was serviced quickly! Dad and I asked him how to keep my car running smoothly and Zack gave me some sound advice. Even though business was already hopping ~10am and things were busy, Zack and team were attentive and nice. I felt at ease the whole time. Most importantly, the crew were very careful with my car during the inspection process.

Keep it up, Flushing Tires! I highly recommend them and calling in advance to do any services. Speak to Zack!<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Wailon H.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="5.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-05-28">
        <p itemprop="description">Zack was a great help. In and out under 10mins for a oil change. All the reviews about quick service are all true.<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Tzlil L.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="5.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2019-02-14">
        <p itemprop="description">Excellent service. The employees are very helpful. They work efficiently and clean. Came in the evening time with my dad when the weather was very cold. We got the tires replaced quickly. Highly recommend them for any service. Very nice and friendly people.<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Art S.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="5.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2017-11-13">
        <p itemprop="description">The flat tire fixing at this location is excellent. I spent about 7 minutes waiting for a spot, then about 7 minutes getting the tire patched. Super fast service. Highly recommend it.

Also, from the little time that I spent here, it seemed like the car repair part of this location was managed by a different person/people from the tire fixing.<p>
    </div>

            <div itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
        <meta itemprop="author" content="Tsz-Cheong C.">
        <div itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
            <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="5.0">
        </div>
        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2015-03-28">
        <p itemprop="description">OH NO! NOT AGAIN! I can&#39;t stand potholes, nails and anything else that ultimately flattens your tire. The winter storms in the Northeast has been brutal to our poor cars.

The only saving grace is the folks at Flushing tire can fix your flat literally in minutes for a very fair and reasonable price.

Whether you opt to apply a patch or a plug on your tire. They will have you in and out quickly.  If you want it done any cheaper, plug it yourself, but $10 for a plug and $15 for a patch is a great price.

If the time ever arises again to fix my tires I will definitely come back here.<p>
    </div>


    </div>

    </div>

